text: Akejan Kajegeldin (; born March 27, 1952), is a Kazakh politician. He was the second Prime Minister of Kazakhstan from October 14, 1994. He resigned on October 10, 1997. He was in President of the Union of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs of Kazakhstan. == References == Category:1952 births Category:Living people Category:Prime ministers of Kazakhstan
